"'''Living Force: Dark Shadows'''" is a short story in the [[Living Force (roleplaying campaign)|''Living Force'' campaign]] for ''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game]]''. It was written by [[August Hahn|August]] and [[Cynthia Hahn]] and was published on the [[Wizards of the Coast]] website on [[February 16]], [[2006]]. It continued the saga of Darrus Jeht, following on from ''[[Dark Hope]]'', and followed by ''[[Living Force: One Minute to Midnight]]''.

==Plot summary==
The Jedi Master [[Darrus Jeht/Legends|Darrus Jeht]] receives orders to attack the Confederacy planet [[Corlax 4]], likely to result in the deaths of millions of civilians. While in transit there, Jeht receives a transmission from was [[Milinae Untaire]]. The smuggler informs him that [[Trilinae Untaire]] has gone missing, as well as that all the Jedi on [[Almas]] have been destroyed. Upon hearing this news, Jeht chooses to disobey his orders and head to the [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]], stopping only to retrieve a shuttle with some of his troops; they, however, have just received [[Order 66/Legends|Order 66]].

